ABSTRACT
A data communication network to provide hop count data
for User Equipment (UE) selection of a wireless relay. The
data communication network comprises a macro base station
and a plurality of wireless relays that serve UEs. The
wireless relays receive a hop count, and in response, incre-
ment their individual hop count and wirelessly broadcast
individual relay Long Term Evolution (LTE) System Infor-
mation Blocks (SIBS) indicating their individual hop counts.
The wireless relays receive wireless UE attachments respon-
sive to the relay LTE SIB broadcasts of their individual hop
counts.
